## Feature ‚Äî lease countdown tooltip on the navbar domain badge

### Context

With the renew-only lease in place, the remaining lease time was invisible.
Added a hover tooltip on the navbar domain badge that shows ‚Äî only while this
browser is the editor ‚Äî a live countdown of the lease (time until expiry if the
tab goes idle). Frontend-only; reuses the Bootstrap `Tooltip` already used
elsewhere (e.g. `permissions.js`).

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js`
   - Track `leaseTtlS` + `lastRenewAt`; `startRenew` records the lease start and
     `doRenew` resets `lastRenewAt` on each confirmed renew (`renewed === true`).
   - `setupLeaseTooltip()` attaches a Bootstrap tooltip to `#currentDomainName`
     (the navbar domain badge) with a dynamic title; it is created only in the
     `mode === "edit"` branch (i.e. only while editing) and only when a lease is
     configured. On `shown.bs.tooltip` a 1s timer refreshes the tooltip content
     (`setContent`) so the `M:SS` countdown ticks live; cleared on hide.
   - `teardownLeaseTooltip()` disposes the tooltip + timer and is called from
     `onLeaseLost` (editing ended ‚Üí tooltip removed).
   - Graceful no-op when Bootstrap's `Tooltip` is unavailable.

### Docs

- `docs/user-guide.md`: single-editor section notes the hover countdown on the
  navbar domain name.

### Modified files

- `src/front/static/global/js/edit-lock.js`
- `docs/user-guide.md`

